    <item>
      <title>美国因涉嫌腐败对奥尔班内阁首席部长罗根实施制裁</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-07/us-sanctions-orban-s-cabinet-chief-rogan-for-alleged-corruption</link>
      <description><![CDATA[就在匈牙利总理维克托·奥尔班的盟友唐纳德·特朗普入主白宫前几天，美国以涉嫌腐败为由对奥尔班极具影响力的内阁首席实施了制裁。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-07/us-sanctions-orban-s-cabinet-chief-rogan-for-alleged-corruption</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 07 Jan 2025 15:48:07 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>尽管政府暂停征税，加拿大仍将实施资本利得税改革</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-07/canada-to-apply-capital-gains-tax-change-despite-government-halt</link>
      <description><![CDATA[尽管加拿大总理贾斯汀·特鲁多暂停议会，但加拿大税务机关将继续适用更高的资本利得纳入税率。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-07/canada-to-apply-capital-gains-tax-change-despite-government-halt</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 07 Jan 2025 15:39:11 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>美国停止打击社交媒体上的暴力极端主义</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-07/us-pulls-back-from-disrupting-violent-extremism-on-social-media</link>
      <description><![CDATA[据现任和前任美国官员以及互联网极端主义专家称，美国联邦调查局和国土安全部在过去两年中已经减少了打击暴力极端分子网络活动的力度，他们担心在即将上任的特朗普政府领导下，这种趋势将会加速。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-07/us-pulls-back-from-disrupting-violent-extremism-on-social-media</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 07 Jan 2025 15:37:11 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>几内亚反对党领袖因侮辱军政府首脑被判入狱</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-07/guinea-jails-opposition-leader-for-insulting-junta-chief</link>
      <description><![CDATA[几内亚法院以侮辱国家过渡总统马马迪·杜姆布亚将军为由，判处反对派领导人马马杜·阿利乌·巴赫两年监禁。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-07/guinea-jails-opposition-leader-for-insulting-junta-chief</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 07 Jan 2025 15:08:01 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>丹麦支持美国对格陵兰岛的投资，但拒绝出售</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-07/denmark-pm-welcomes-us-role-in-greenland-after-trump-interest</link>
      <description><![CDATA[丹麦首相梅特·弗雷德里克森拒绝了美国当选总统唐纳德·特朗普购买格陵兰岛的愿望，但欢迎美国对该自治领土的投资。]]></description>
